availability-zones-820.md:An availability zone is an organisational unit containing nodes, where each node is in exactly one zone. While in production, a machine can be allocated from a specific zone.  Availability zones can be used for fault-tolerance, service performance, and power management. See [Zone examples](/t/zone-examples/784) for more details.
