commissioning-and-hardware-testing-scripts-833.md:When selecting multiple machines in the [web UI](/t/node-overview/829), scripts which declare the `for_hardware` field will only run on machines with matching hardware. To automatically run a script when 'Update firmware' or 'Configure HBA' is selected, you must tag the script with 'update_firmware' or 'configure_hba'.
commissioning-and-hardware-testing-scripts-833.md:Similarly, scripts selected by tag on the [command line](/t/cli-testing-scripts/832) which specify the `for_hardware` field will only run on matching hardware.
commissioning-and-hardware-testing-scripts-833.md:A status message of Commissioning script created will appear.  You'll then be able to select your script after selecting [Test hardware](/t/hardware-testing/826) from a machine's 'Take action' menu.
commissioning-and-hardware-testing-scripts-833.md:As long as you've added your [SSH key](/t/user-accounts/790#heading--ssh-keys) to MAAS, you can connect with SSH to the machine's IP with a username of `ubuntu`. Type `sudo -i` to get root access.
commissioning-and-hardware-testing-scripts-833.md:For information about managing scripts, applying tags to scripts and seeing script results using the CLI, please see [CLI Testing Scripts](/t/cli-testing-scripts/832).
commissioning-logs-1478.md:Each of the items in the "NAME" column is the name of a [commissioning script](/t/commission-machines/822#heading--commissioning-scripts).  Each entry gives a timestamp and a result (e.g. passed, failed, ...). At the end of each line is a link to view the log. It's worth taking a look at each of the script logs and their typical output.
