high-availability-804.md:1.  Set up PostgreSQL for high-availability as [explained above](/t/high-availability/804#heading--postgresql-ha). PostgreSQL should run outside of the snap.
high-availability-804.md:2.  [Install](/t/install-from-a-snap/773#heading--install-from-snap) the MAAS snap on each machine you intend to use as a rack or region controller. You'll need the MAAS shared secret, located here, `/var/lib/maas/secret`, on the first region controller you set up.
high-availability-804.md:3.  [Initialise the snap](/t/install-from-a-snap/773#heading--initialisation) as a `rack` or `region` controller. Note that if you intend to use a machine as a region controller, you'll need to tell MAAS how to access your PostgreSQL database host with the following arguments:
