kvm-host-networking-807.md:If the [MAAS deployed a host](/t/add-a-kvm-h-ost/805) for use as a KVM host (recommended), MAAS will skip the libvirt `maas` and `default` networks if they are not enabled for DHCP in MAAS, instead preferring a DHCP-enabled MAAS network. This arrangement means you don't have to manually create a MAAS-friendly libvirt network to which to attach the VM as with previous versions of MAAS.
